<td colspan=2 bgcolor="#0000AF"><font color=white>Just to answer a few points raised<BR>
<BR>
a)  the people who would sell em are none warriors - Cobolt  Stuff is warrior only - why would a necro wanit for  instance<BR>
<BR>
b)  the cobolt stuff has a long cast time.  This is fairly obvious to me on the basis that warriors are casters.<BR>
<BR>
c) cobolt stuff has been introduced to swing the balance of power back - its one of the facts that there is only the rogue and warrior who cant really solo.  Why???? cos we cant heal and cant root.  <BR>
<BR>
d) Any warrior who has Cobolt Stuff before lvl 45(more likely 47+)is either a big twink, an excellent tradesman, a<BR>
ninja looter or VERY fortunate.  To obtain the gloves for instance before lvl 45 is virtual suicide. I acquired em at<BR>
51.<BR>
<BR>
e) Cobolt stuff is definitely dropped in both Sebilis and Karnor and consists of most parts. I know that the boots and gloves are very rare.<BR>
<BR>
Hope this answers a few questions <BR>
